descriptionMarkdown:
A way to maintain supplies at outposts.  Set the supply levels in the constant combinator, It will also ship “junk” items from the outpost to the main base.
To work the green wire at each unloading station needs to be connected to the green wire at the loading station.

Requires Green wire from all the outposts to the sending/filling station.  The filling station will take all outpost requests together for loading onto the train.

The train schedule should be:
“Outpost Auto Load” (the station in your main base near your mall that the train will load at)
-	Circuit R >= 1 
-	AND 
-	5s of inactivity
-	OR 
-	Full cargo inventory

“Outpost Auto Unload” (the station(s) in your outpost(s) to receive supplies)
-	Circuit R = 0 
-	OR 
-	5s of inactivity
All the outposts to be serviced should be named the same.
Outpost stations that need no supplies will be disabled and bypassed by the train, so only one “Outpost Auto Unload” stop in the schedule is needed for as many Outposts as you have.
If you want to speed up service when multiple outposts need supplies at the same time add multiple “Outpost Auto Unload” stops in the schedule.  

The constant combinator next to “REQ” is the setting for what the receiver logistic networks will maintain, asking for anything that is missing.  The blueprint has 3 combinators providing input requests.

Tips
-	There are two roboports on the receiving side.  One reports supply levels in the logistics network, the other reports bot levels.  
-	Keep the bot requests low on the constant combinator – this is for the # of bots in storage.  Set the # of active bots on the two inserters inserting into the roboport.
-	“Outpost Auto Unload” train stop can be repeated to have the train stop at more than one station per run.

Version
-	1.0 - used filter inserters - didn't work right with large number of required items.
-	2.0 - CURRENT - uses regular inserters and signals to enable/disable.  No know bugs.  Let me know if you find any.
title: Logistics Restocker for Outposts via Trains
